19.0 Compensation day
.br
:SKRSLUT.
:SWISS8.
Insurance sum: DKK 25,000 per person and max. DKK 75,000 per claim.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED
19.1 Coverage
:SKRSLUT.
.br
The coverage provides financial compensation for the number of days of the
travel that are ruined if the insured:
.br
- suffers acute illness or injury that results in hospitalisation
.br
.kp off
.kp on
- is medically ordered to rest in and around the holiday residence on
account of acute illness or injury
.br
.kp off
.kp on
- is repatriated in accordance with written instructions from the
attending physician
.br
- has been obliged to discontinue the journey, see Article 7.0.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
19.1.1 If the doctor's note from the local attending physician
does not make it directly clear that the insured has been
prescribed hospitalisation or rest in and around the holiday
residence, Privatsikring's doctor will asses whether the
insurance provides coverage on the basis of the information
available.
.br
In the event of doubt regarding the applicable period of
hospitalisation or rest, the issue will be decided by Privatsikring's
doctor.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED
19.2 Calculation of the number of travel days
:SKRSLUT.
:FED.
19.4 Reporting claims
:SKRSLUT.
.br
The claim is to be filed with Privatsikring on returning home. The
compensation liability is conditional upon the insured himself/herself
obtaining a doctor's note containing a diagnosis and information about the
duration of the bed rest/medically prescribed rest in and around the
holiday residence.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
In the event of interrupted travel (see Article 7.0), it is also a
condition that Privatsikring receive acceptable documentation if
Privatsikring's doctor has not approved repatriation/travel home in
advance. The doctor's note and documentation of expenses paid are to be
submitted to Privatsikring.
.sp 5mm
.kp off
.br
The travel period is calculated in whole days. The number of travel days
ruined is calculated as follows:
.br
- From midnight on the day after the first doctor's visit up to and
including the date of discharge or the end of the period of rest.
.br
.kp off
.kp on
- From midnight on the day after the insured was repatriated or travelled
home on account of an incident covered by Article 7.0.
.br
.kp off
.kp on
- The days of departure and return are considered two complete
days, irrespective of the time of day.
.br
- Compensation will not be paid for the day of return travel, and never
over and above the original travel period.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
19.3 Compensation
:SKRSLUT.
.br
A set sum will be paid per day of travel ruined.
.br
Compensation will be calculated as the sum that the insured has paid to
the travel organiser for the travel. Compensation will only be paid to
cover expenses for meals if these are included in the travel price.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
In the event of individually organised travel, compensation will be
limited to documented non-refundable expenses for transport and
accommodation. For car travel, a price will be calculated per km
driven on the shortest route from the insured's domicile to the
destination and back. The sum will be calculated on the basis of the
Danish State rates for mileage in own vehicle in excess of 20,000 km
per year. If not everyone in the vehicle is covered by this insurance
- see Article 1.0 - the expenses will be divided proportionally.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
The maximum compensation payable for compensation days is DKK 25,000 per
person, and no more than DKK 75,000 per claim.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
